                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.68in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.58in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Disconnect connector (1060). Move key switch to ignition position. Measure voltage
                                from circuit 75BE to ground while sliding the temperature control from one extreme to
                                the other.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>(1060), circuit 75BE to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>The voltage should vary as the control is varied.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of incorrect voltage in circuit 75BE, from HVAC control (1057), then
                                repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Reconnect connector (1060). Remove the connector to the cab stepper motor in the
                                heater box. Turn ignition on. Measure the voltage between circuit 75BE and ground as the
                                temperature control is varied.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Between circuit 75BE and ground as the temperature control is varied.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>The voltage should vary as the control is varied.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of incorrect voltage in circuit 75BE, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>At cab stepper motor connector, measure voltage from circuit 75BJ to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Locate cause of incorrect voltage in circuit 75BJ, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>12 &#177; 1.5 volts.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate cause of incorrect voltage in circuit 75BJ, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Measure resistance from cab stepper motor connector circuit 75-GL to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Cab stepper motor connector circuit 75-GL to ground.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Locate open in circuit 75-GL, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>7.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Off/ On</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Re-install the cab stepper motor connector. Turn ignition on. Check if the stepper
                                motor operates while the temperature control is varied from on extreme to the other.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Stepper motor operates.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Cab tem- pera- ture controls check good.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Replace cab stepper motor.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
